Actress Nkechi Blessing and her husband Hon Opeyemi Falegan have confirmed the end of their one-year marriage. They confirmed their split on Instagram live with hostilies. On her Instagram live, NBS, as she’s fondly called, alleged Falegan is a jobless politician who has time to go on IG live every time. She said: “I have a large family and I cannot come and be using this small money I’m seeing to feed a grown man. Leave my name out of your mouth. “If dem ask me say wetin my so-called boyfriend does for a living walahi I don’t have an answer. ” Three weeks in London, you no wake up go work, sleep and wake up for live video, if joblessness was a person. “The one wey I no go like na if you lie say you leave me, leave me? Nobody does! I simply take a walk and say my side of the story because really it’s not worth it.   Hisbah seizes 1,426 bottles of alcoholic beverages     Gunmen kill two, injure others in Plateau IDPs camp     Journalists launch book on experiences of campus reporters   “Say what you like but you see lie, we go wear the same trousers. Na then gangan you go vex me. “You made me almost fight everybody because na only you all my colleagues wan fuck. “Meanwhile, na you dey their DM oh dey find favour, you wan use me still use the people close to me, as I no gree, problem started. ” In your words: “what will it cost you to get this person to do a video for my foundation.” On his part, Falegan, in a live video, said he doesn’t want to be known or addressed as Nkechi’s husband. “What I want to be known for is someone who has added value to the people, who will keep doing the good work for the people. ” I have a name to protect. I don’t want to be known with any notoriety, any little thing ‘oko’ (husband), please guys put respect on my name.”